# Scenario Graph

Each persona = one finite state machine in `src/scenarios/graphs/{scenario-id}.json`.

## Node Fields (required)

```json
{
  "node_id": "approach-dm",
  "app_type": "instagram",
  "required_risk_signal": "급격한 친밀감, 비밀 요구",
  "forbidden_content": ["실제 성적 묘사", "실존 인물 사칭"],
  "next_node_map": { "safe": "report", "warn": "threaten", "danger": "exploit" },
  "timer_seconds": 30,
  "voice_enabled": false
}
```

## Rules

- `next_node_map` keys must be: `safe` | `warn` | `danger` | `neutral`
- Teen scenarios (`teen-*`): always `"voice_enabled": false`
- Graph changes = JSON edit + deploy; LLM prompts reference `node_id`
- Never let LLM invent nodes — only traverse `next_node_map`

## Persona Matching

Logic in `src/lib/scenario/persona-matching.ts` — see `docs/product-planning.md` table.
